{DIALOGUE}: I hear you like to hit women.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PRISONER
{DIALOGUE}: My wife.
{DIALOGUE}: She's dropping charges so it's none of your business.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud enters, closes the door behind him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A beat, we hear the sounds of FISTS ON FLESH.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's Bud's business now.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BEVERLY HILLS MANSION - STUDY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Deuce Perkins (the Mickey Cohen narcotics lieutenant seen earlier) stands at the bookshelf.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls down books to reveal a shoe box.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sets it on his desk, pulls back the cover to reveal several bags of white powder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Heroin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A BRANCH SNAPS outside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Perkins opens a drawer, fishes a revolver.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Turning off the light, he heads to the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His finger parts the curtains.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At that instant, he staggers, falls as GUNFIRE rips into him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The heroin just sits there on the desk.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. McNEIL PENITENTIARY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Grim-faced guards scan the yard from machine-gunned towers.
