{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. NITE OWL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley takes mental snapshots.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ten stools front a counter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The side wall mural-papered: winking owls perched on street signs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the right a string of tables.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Three in disarray.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Food spilled, dishes broken.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A high-heel pump by an upended chair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Heel drag marks across the linoleum floor heading back toward the kitchen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley follows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Past an open, empty cash register.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Outside -- SIRENS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SERVICE RUNWAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Crisscrossed drag marks connect, lead to a walk-in...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FOOD LOCKER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Blood-soaked bodies on the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Five, maybe six in a tangle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dozens of shotgun shells float in the pools of blood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Exley struggles to maintain his composure...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROOKIE (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Holy shit fuck...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley looks at a green-faced ROOKIE in the locker doorway.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROOKIE
