{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Don't get sick!
{DIALOGUE}: Not in here!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley shoves the Rookie, puking, out the door.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NITE OWL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Patrolmen hold back a swarm of reporters and rubber- neckers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HORNS BLAST.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Motorcycles run interference for meat wagons cut off by the crown.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Ed emerges, reporters surge, shout questions.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley hurries past, finds Dudley in command and barking orders.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Sir, I took the call.
{DIALOGUE}: It's my case.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Edmund, you don't want it and you can't have it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, I do, sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: It's mine.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll make you my second in command.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley spots a photographer moving in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks properly serious as the flash bulb pops.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. NIGHT OWL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forensics Chief RAY PINKER walks Exley and Dudley through.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PINKER
{DIALOGUE}: We got a total of forty-five spent 12-gauge Remington shotgun shells.
{DIALOGUE}: Three men with five-shot-capacity pumps.
{DIALOGUE}: All of them reloading twice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Hold on... We need to canvass.
{DIALOGUE}: See if a purple Mercury was seen around here tonight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Why?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: We got a call earlier on three Negro youths.
{DIALOGUE}: Firing shotguns in Griffith Park from a late-model purple Mercury Coupe.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{META_DATA}: (to his adjutant)
{DIALOGUE}: Get on it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A FORENSICS COP approaches Pinker.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORENSICS COP
{DIALOGUE}: We got an I.D. on one of the victims, sir... I think it's Dick Stensland.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley and Dudley react, look at each other.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VICTORY MOTEL - DAWN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Set in a no-man's-land of bulldozed homes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A sign proudly announces the impending arrival of the freeway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The motel is surrounded by a barbed-wire fence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Abandoned but for a pair of LAPD cars and a light burning in room 6.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An unmarked pulls up and Exley and Dudley step out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They start forward, but a SCREAM inside 6 stops Exley short.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: With Mickey Cohen in prison, Los Angeles is organized crime free.
{DIALOGUE}: The Chief wants it to stay that way, Edmund.
{DIALOGUE}: The means are not for the weak-hearted.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. VICTORY MOTEL - ROOM 6 - DAWN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bare.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A table and chair bolted to the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A tough FLAT-NOSED GANGSTER is cuffed to the hot seat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the table are a .45 and a fat roll of $100 bills.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Breuning and Carlisle watch as Bud White delivers a couple of short, stiff body shots.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Flatnose is not used to being on the receiving end.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All the same, we get the idea Bud's a bit reluctant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud's back is to Dudley and Exley who enter behind him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Come, Wendell, you can do better than that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud turns, sees Exley and Dudley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Bud looms over Flatnose, the gangster babbles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Snitch-frenzied.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FLATNOSE
{DIALOGUE}: I know things.
{DIALOGUE}: I hear things.
{DIALOGUE}: Like with the Mick inside, things are on this weird slowdown.
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FLATNOSE (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: These shooter teams, bang bang bang, they're 86-ing Mickey Cohen's men.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: We know all that, lad.
{DIALOGUE}: Tell us, who do these shooters work for?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FLATNOSE
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know.
{DIALOGUE}: No one knows.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe they're mavericks.
{DIALOGUE}: You want a prostie roust?
{DIALOGUE}: Huh?
{DIALOGUE}: Some narco action?
{META_DATA}: (breaking down)
{DIALOGUE}: What do you want?!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: We want you to go home.
{META_DATA}: (to Breuning)
{DIALOGUE}: Uncuff him, Michael.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley turns to Exley.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Sifakis is a known loan shark from San Francisco.
{DIALOGUE}: He arrived this afternoon at Union Station.
{DIALOGUE}: Looking for business opportunities in our fair city.
{DIALOGUE}: An organized crime associate in need of re- education in the ways of polite society.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Uncuffed, Flatnose rubs his wrists.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wary.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Breuning steps back, Flatnose snatches the .45 off the table.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FLATNOSE
{DIALOGUE}: Motherfuckers!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley dives for cover, but the other four cops just stand there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley looks down on the floor at Exley.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: It's part of the play, Edmund.
{DIALOGUE}: A sincerity test.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Flatnose looks at the gun a beat, then squeezes the TRIGGER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLICK CLICK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No bullets.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{META_DATA}: (to Breuning)
{DIALOGUE}: Sit him back down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLICK, CLICK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They shove Flatnose back in the hot seat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley offers a hand to Exley, helps him to his feet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Wendell, you need to accompany Detective Lieutenant Exley on official police business.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll finish up here.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. EXLEY'S PLYMOUTH - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They drive in silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No love lost here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Where are we going?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: It's a surprise.
{DIALOGUE}: You like surprises, don't you, White?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. COUNTY MORGUE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley pulls up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud looks to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Really curious now.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. COUNTY MORGUE - HALLWAY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley and Bud walk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An orderly wheels a covered corpse toward them from the other end of the hall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud's spooked.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The orderly wheels the body in to the examination room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Bud and Exley pass, the CORONER pulls back the sheet, is surprised at the sight of a woman who we don't quite see.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CORONER
{DIALOGUE}: Call me crazy, but for a second I thought it was Rita Hayworth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MORGUE MEAT LOCKER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley and Bud walk past a wall of drawers to where a coroner's assistant waits.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: We need you to I.D. the body.
{DIALOGUE}: There's no next of kin and you knew him best.
{DIALOGUE}: So tell me...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The assistant pulls open drawer 12.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A naked man.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A tag on his toe and half his face blown off.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Is that Dick Stensland?
