{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, that's Stens.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Hell of a way to avoid a prison sentence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud's torn between wanting to smash Exley and finding out why Stensland is dead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He squeezes out the words.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: What happened?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Someone held up a coffee shop, panicked and killed six people.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then, from the hall...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WOMAN (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Not my baby!
{DIALOGUE}: Not my little girl!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. COUNTY MORGUE - EXAMINATION ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HILDA LEFFERTS, 50, enters with the coroner to ID the body of her daughter, Susan.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's stray buckshot in the upper chest and shoulders, but a sheet hides the real damage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's the girl Bud saw outside Hollywood Liquor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Without the black eyes, she does look like Rita hayworth.
