{DIALOGUE}: Dear God...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Mrs. Lefferts swoons, Bud and Exley both hold her up.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LAPD HEADQUARTERS - BRIEFING ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The room buzzes, jammed to the rafters with every detective standing ready.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Chief waits as Dudley Smith takes the mike, holds up an L.A. Times headline.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: 'Nite Owl Massacre.'
{DIALOGUE}: Hyperbole aside, this is a heinous crime that requires a swift resolution.
{DIALOGUE}: The public will demand it and this department will provide it.
{DIALOGUE}: Six victims.
{DIALOGUE}: One of them, one of our own -- Dick Stensland.
{META_DATA}: (as the cops react)
{DIALOGUE}: As it happens, he was a Nite Owl regular.
{DIALOGUE}: In the wrong place at the wrong time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud White listens, not too sure.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stensland said he had something big going on...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Robbery looks like the motive.
{DIALOGUE}: We have rubber glove prints on the register and preliminary forensics strongly lean toward a trio of gunmen.
{DIALOGUE}: We do have one hot lead, so listen well.
{DIALOGUE}: Three Negro youths were seen last night discharging shotguns in the air at Griffith Park.
{DIALOGUE}: A park ranger I.D.ed them as driving a 1948 to 1950 Mercury Coupe, purple in color.
{DIALOGUE}: An hour ago, a canvassing crew found a news vendor who saw a purple Merc Coupe parked across from the Nite Owl around 3:00 A.M.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The room goes loud, a big rumbling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley holds up a list.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: The D.M.V. worked all night to get us a registration list on '48 to '50 purple Mercs.
{DIALOGUE}: There are 142 registered to Negroes in L.A. County.
{DIALOGUE}: Fifty two-man teams will shake three names apiece.
{DIALOGUE}: Hot suspects you'll bring here.
{DIALOGUE}: Interrogation rooms have been set up.
{DIALOGUE}: They'll be run by Lieutenant Edmund Exley.
{DIALOGUE}: Hollywood Squad.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Catcalls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boos.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Chief steps to the mike.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHIEF
