{DIALOGUE}: Lynn Bracken is one of them and so was Susan Lefferts.
{DIALOGUE}: I treat my girls very well.
{DIALOGUE}: I have grown daughters, myself, and I don't like the thought of women being hurt.
{DIALOGUE}: I sense you share this feeling.
{META_DATA}: BUD (ignores comment)
{DIALOGUE}: Why were Lefferts' eyes black?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PATCHETT
{DIALOGUE}: I think she'd been hit in the face with a tennis racket.
{DIALOGUE}: She is -- was -- a big doubles fan.
