{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: That's right.
{DIALOGUE}: Our motives are selfish, so we're cooperating.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Why was Susan Lefferts at the Nite Owl?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know.
{DIALOGUE}: I never heard of the Nite Owl till today.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Did Lefferts have a boyfriend?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Like I said we were friendly, not friends.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: How'd she meet Patchett?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Pierce meets people.
{DIALOGUE}: Sue came on the bus with dreams of Hollywood.
{DIALOGUE}: This is how they turned out.
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks to Pierce, we still get to act a little.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me about Patchett.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: He's waiting for you to mention mention.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: You want some advice, Miss Bracken?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: It's Lynn.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Miss Bracken, don't ever try to fucking bribe me or threaten me or I'll have you and Patchett in shit up to your ears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn smiles again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She likes Bud.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: I remember you from Christmas Eve.
{DIALOGUE}: You have a thing for helping women, don't you, Officer White?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe I'm just fucking curious.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: You say 'fuck' a lot.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: You fuck for money.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: There's blood on your shirt.
{DIALOGUE}: Is that an integral part of your job?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Do you enjoy it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: When they deserve it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Did they deserve it today?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not sure.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: But you did it anyway.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, just like the half dozen guys you screwed today.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{META_DATA}: (laughs again)
{DIALOGUE}: Actually, it was two.
{DIALOGUE}: You're different, Officer White.
{DIALOGUE}: You're the first man in five years who didn't tell me I look like Veronica Lake inside of a minute.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: You look better than Veronica Lake.
{DIALOGUE}: Now, Pierce Patchett.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: He takes a cut of our earnings and invests it for us.
{DIALOGUE}: He makes us quit the life at thirty.
{DIALOGUE}: He doesn't let us use narcotics and he doesn't abuse us.
{DIALOGUE}: Can your policeman's mentality grasp those contradictions?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: He had you cut to look like Veronica Lake?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm really a brunette, but the rest is me.
{DIALOGUE}: And that's all the news that's fit to print.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn starts toward the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud watches her a moment, then follows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She takes his glass at the door.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: It was nice meeting you, Officer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Out the door, Bud turns back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Blurts:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Look.
{DIALOGUE}: I want to see you again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Are you asking me for a date or an appointment?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{META_DATA}: (suddenly unsure)
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{META_DATA}: (another smile)
{DIALOGUE}: If it's a date I think you'd better tell me your first name because I --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{META_DATA}: (feeling foolish)
{DIALOGUE}: Forget I asked.
{DIALOGUE}: It was a mistake.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn watches thoughtfully after Bud as he walks away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He opens his car door like he's going to tear ir off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A last glance back at Lynn and as he gets in the car...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. TEVERE HOTEL - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An L-shaped walk-up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack coasts the car to the curb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leaps out with Exley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley holds up at the sight of a late model sedan.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leans down to look in the window at the two-way on the dash.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: L.A.P.D.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Shit.
{DIALOGUE}: Someone beat us here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VOICES from the carport ahead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see a chrome bumper, the purple fender of a '49 Mercury coupe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A door slams.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Drawing a .45, Jack starts over with Exley, .38 in hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CARPORT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toting shotguns, Dudley's boys from the Victory Motel, Breuning and Carlisle, stand by the purple Mercury.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack and Exley come around the corner, lower their guns.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Hey.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Breuning wheels, pumps a round into the chamber.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He very nearly fires before he sees who it is.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARLISLE
{DIALOGUE}: What the fuck are you guys doing here?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Think of us as back-up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: What do you got?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Jack moves to peer through the Merc's window.
