{DIALOGUE}: Just don't shoot me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door to 414.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two men on either side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Breuning rears back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack rears back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They kick at the same instant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door flies off its hinges to reveal two young black men, LARRY FONTAINE and TY JONES, waking from a couple of flop mattresses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ROOM 414
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fontaine jumps up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Entering, Carlisle aims, but Exley grabs his arm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The BLAST rips the ceiling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack aims.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Freeze!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fontaine freezes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jones doesn't dare get up.
