{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Satisfied, Exley sets the report down.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Ed, I want confessions.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: I'll break them, sir.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Exley steps into the #1 room, Jack joins Dudley.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: You think golden boy can handle it, Cap?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: I think you'll be surprised what Edmund's capable of.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. #1 ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley closes the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ray Coates is cuffed to a chair, dressed in baggy County denims.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One eye swollen shut, lip split, a smashed nose with one nostril split.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley unlocks his cuffs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: drops cigarettes and amtches on the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Coates rubs his wrists...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: They call you Sugar Ray because of Ray Robinson?
{META_DATA}: (no answer)
{DIALOGUE}: They say Robinson can throw a four punch combination in one second.
{DIALOGUE}: Do you believe that?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coates just stares at him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: You're twenty-two, aren't you, Ray?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COATES
{DIALOGUE}: Say what and so what.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Did one of the officers work you over a little?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No bite.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coates just stares back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: You look like Robinson after that last LaMotta fight.
{DIALOGUE}: 'Course LaMotta looked a lot worse.
{DIALOGUE}: So you're twenty-two, right?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COATES
{DIALOGUE}: Man, why do you keep asking me that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Just getting my facts straight.
{DIALOGUE}: Twenty-two makes it a gas chamber bounce.
{DIALOGUE}: You should have pulled this caper a couple of years ago.
{DIALOGUE}: Get life, do a little Youth Authority jolt, transfer to Folsom a big man.
{DIALOGUE}: Orbit on some of that good prison brew, get yourself a sissy --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COATES
{DIALOGUE}: I never truck with no sissies!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: That fucking Larry.
{DIALOGUE}: I almost believed him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COATES
{DIALOGUE}: Believed what?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Nothing, Ray.
{META_DATA}: (laughs)
{DIALOGUE}: That Larry, he's a pisser.
{DIALOGUE}: You did the Casitas Youth Camp with him, didn't you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COATES
{DIALOGUE}: Man, why're you talkin' about Larry?
{DIALOGUE}: His business is his business.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Unseen by Coates, Exley reaches under the table, takes hold of one of three toggle switches.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Sugar, Larry told me you went sissy up at Casitas.
{DIALOGUE}: You couldn't do the time so you found yourself a big white boy to look after you.
{DIALOGUE}: He said they call you 'Sugar' because you gave it out so sweet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley flips the toggle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: #3 ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The speaker over Larry Fontaine's head crackles to life.
