{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Where is she now?
{META_DATA}: (no answer)
{DIALOGUE}: Did you leave her someplace?
{META_DATA}: (no answer)
{DIALOGUE}: Did you sell her out?
{DIALOGUE}: Give her to some of your buddies?
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me where the girl is!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door blasts open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud slams Jones up against the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Exley stands, he bangs his knee on the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pulling a .38, Bud breaks the cylinder, drops 5 shells on the floor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: One in six.
{DIALOGUE}: Where's the girl?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Officer White, put down that weapon and --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud shoves the barrel into Jones' mouth, pulls the trigger twice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLICK, CLICK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jones starts to slide down the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud jerks him back up, roars.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: WHERE?!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two more clicks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jones spills.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JONES
{DIALOGUE}: S-sylvester F-fitch one-o-nine and Avalon gray corner house...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. AVALON BOULEVARD - EVENING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A four cordon.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They coast up to a GRAY CORNER HOUSE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley Smith behind the wheel of the lead cruiser.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud White rides shotgun, reloading his revolver.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Give me one minute.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: You've got it, Wendell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: STREET
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud is out the door and scooting down an alley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley moves to follow, but Dudley cuts him off.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: We're going through the front.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ALLEY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud vaults a fence, pads up the back porch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A screen door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud slips the catch with a penknife and walks inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SCREEN PORCH
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud heads for a blind-covered door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Unlocked, he enters...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A HALLWAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Light bouncing from side rooms.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear the opening spiel of "Badge of Honor" from the left.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud wheels into a..
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BEDROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A NUDE GIRL spread-eagled on a mattress.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bound with neckties.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One in her mouth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her eyes grow wide at the sight of Bud, then flicker to the adjoining room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Directing him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Raising the .38, Bud enters...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE KITCHEN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sylvester Fitch sits naked at the table wolfing Rice Krispies and watching "Badge of Honor" on a flickering TV.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks up, sees the .38 before he sees Bud beyond it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fitch drops his spoon, raises his hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud SHOOTS him in the face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dead, Fitch just sits there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud moves behind him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pulling a spare piece from an ankle holster, Bud FIRES back at the door from Fitch's line of fire, then puts the gun in Fitch's hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear the FRONT DOOR CRASH OPEN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Fitch slides off the chair to the floor, Bud dumps the Rice Krispies on him.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. GRAY HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Girl on a stretcher.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Being carried to an AMBULANCE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud White walks alongside, looking like some ferocious pet pit bull.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ATTENDANTS get her inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One joins her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other closes the door, pauses to light a smoke.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud rips the cigarette out of his mouth, nearly taking the guy's lips with it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Get her to the fucking hospital.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One look at Bud, and the Attendant is running around to the driver's side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley arrives, steamed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: A naked guy with a gun?
{DIALOGUE}: You expect anyone to believe that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Get the fuck away from me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud starts away, but Exley gets right in his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Other cops begin to take notice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ambulance pulls out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: How's it going to look on your report?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: It'll look like justice.
{DIALOGUE}: That's what that fat fuck got.
{DIALOGUE}: Justice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: You don't know what the word means, you dumb bastard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud goes after Exley, but ten hands pull them apart.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley on Exley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Four cops genuinely having trouble on Bud.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And as if things couldn't get crazier, shouts from the cops on the street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: POLICE RADIOS CRANKED UP.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DISPATCHER (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Repeat, three suspects escaped from the Hall of Justice jail.
{DIALOGUE}: The Nite Owl killers: Raymond Coates, Tyrone Jones and Larry Fontaine.
{DIALOGUE}: They are considered armed and extremely dangerous.
{DIALOGUE}: Descriptions are as follows...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SQUAD ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Electrified, "Nite Owl Killers" on everyone's lips.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley strides through with purpose, beelines to a filing cabinet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley pulls the file he's looking for.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He scans an interrogation transcript, reads to himself the words he's looking for:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: 'Give me one to feed the D.A.... Roland Navarette.
{DIALOGUE}: Lives on Bunker Hill.
{DIALOGUE}: Runs a hole-up for parole absconders.'
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOLLYWOOD STATION - JACK'S DESK - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Police rush back and forth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley hurries over to the desk, but he's not there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Anyone seen Jack Vincennes?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A few cops mumble they haven't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Exley decides what to do, Carlisle from the original arrest steps over.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARLISLE
{DIALOGUE}: Is something up, Lieutenant?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. 1ST & OLIVE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley and Carlisle pull up across the street from a four-story Victorian with paint peeling off the clap- boards.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They jump out of the car toting SHOTGUNS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carlisle waits as Exley checks the mail slots: "R. Navarette, 408. "
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. STAIRWELL - VICTORIAN BUILDING - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley and Carlisle take the steps two at a time.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. 4TH FLOOR HALLWAY - VICTORIAN BUILDING - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley squints, reaches to a pocket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No glasses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He passes an elevator, rounds a corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's 408.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley pumps the shotgun, nods to Carlisle who kicks the door in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NAVARETTE LIVING ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley and Carlisle burst in on four men eating sandwiches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fontaine and Caucasian NAVARETTE at a table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coates on the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jones by the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley squints.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Nobody move!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fontaine and Navarette raise their hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A jostled BEER BOTTLE CRASHES to the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reacting, Carlisle JERKS the TRIGGER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fontaine goes down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Navarette draws a .38, SHOOTS Carlisle twice in the chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley BLASTS Navarette.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Screaming, Jones pulls a .45 from his belt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley FIRES, blowing him right THROUGH the WINDOW.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coates draws and FIRES, makes a run for it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A bad pull takes out half a back wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coates is out the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ELEVATOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coates makes it inside, frantically pushes buttons.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HALLWAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Here comes Exley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stumbling, wiping Navarette's blood out of his eyes, he closes on the...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ELEVATOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coates watches as the elevator doors begin closing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HALLWAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley charging.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ELEVATOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The shotgun barrel juts through.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The doors bang against it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BLAM!
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: L.A. MONTAGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TONY BENNETT belts "BOULEVARD OF BROKEN DREAMS."
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOLLYWOOD STATION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley returns to grudging respect.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His white shirt flecked with blood, he's clapped on the back by Dudley who dubs him "Shotgun Ed."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley doesn't enjoy it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's numb, stumbling along.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he notices the blood on his hands...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT - NEWSPAPER HEADLINE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NITE OWL HERO!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Over a photo of Exley.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. CEMETERY - GRAVE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A coffin is lowered into the ground.
