{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. 1736 NOTTINGHAM (LYNN BRACKEN'S) - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rain.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A limo disgorges a heavy-set man who climbs steps, knocks on the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn answers in an evening gown.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gives her a peck on the cheek and continues in past her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn's about to follow him in when she pauses to deadpan a look down the street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud's Packard is parked there and we can see his darkened silhouette behind the wheel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Smiling a bit sadly to herself, Lynn disappears inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is no stake-out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud watches after her with yearning.
