{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As she locks eyes with him an instant...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PIERCE PATCHETT'S HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The monied johns watch horny as hell as "Ginger Rogers" twirls around the room with a female "Fred Astaire."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clothes fly as they spin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Still, most eyes turn to Lynn Bracken as she enters oozing that cat-girl grace.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. POLICE HEADQUARTERS - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reporters scribble as the Chief speaks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Uniforms everywhere along with Exley and Loew.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bus sits in the back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHIEF
{DIALOGUE}: Edmund J. Exley has amassed a brilliant record in his seven years with the L.A.P.D. Recently he evinced spectacular bravery in the line of duty.
{DIALOGUE}: It is my honor to present him with our highest honor, the Medal of Valor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley steps up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Chief hangs a gold medallion around his neck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Flashbulbs pop as the two men shake hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley then accepts a handshake from Dudley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The policemen stand on cue, applaud without enthusiasm.
