{DIALOGUE}: Matched forensically.
{DIALOGUE}: A few loose ends don't matter.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Something's wrong.
{DIALOGUE}: I feel it inside.
{DIALOGUE}: Doesn't that sound crazy?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley puts an arm around Exley's shoulder, smiles out as more bulbs flash.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Breaking a big case sticks you in a whirlwind.
{DIALOGUE}: A little self-doubt?
{DIALOGUE}: It's natural.
{DIALOGUE}: Just keep it inside.
{DIALOGUE}: Between you and you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley considers his medal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is an appealing thing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the back, Bud stays sprawled in his seat.
