{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. VICTORY HOTEL - ROOM SIX - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Screams.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A cauliflower-eared Cleveland mob enforcer on the hotseat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Breuning works him with a rubber hose as Dudley asks unanswered questions.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud watches, revulsion growing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Where did you intend to start.
{DIALOGUE}: Prostitution?
{DIALOGUE}: Gambling?
{META_DATA}: (no answer)
{DIALOGUE}: Go back to Cleveland, lad.
{DIALOGUE}: This is the City of Angels and you haven't got any wings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: More screams as the hose thwops down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud looks away, then shuffles blindly out of the room.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. VICTORY HOTEL - BATHROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud runs water in the sink to drown out the SCREAMS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It doesn't work.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally, he leans down and sticks his head under the stream of water.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: That doesn't work either.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VICTORY HOTEL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hair dripping wet, Bud makes it to his car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The tires spit gravel as he tears away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley appears in the doorway, watching curiously.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As cauliflower continues to SCREAM...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BUD'S PACKARD - 1736 NOTTINGHAM (LYNN'S) - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud watches Lynn Bracken's apartment, Colored lights play on the windows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shadows pass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally the front door opens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's Veronica Lake, all sparkles and spangles, kissing another distinguished gentleman goodnight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud watches the man into a waiting limo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As it pulls away...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. 1736 NOTTINGHAM (LYNN BRACKEN'S) - LIVING ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now Lynn just looks tired.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As she puts away Scotch bottles and picks up empty glasses, there's a KNOCK on the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn sighs, become sultry Veronica Lake before our eyes.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FRONT HALL - NIGHT
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{META_DATA}: (opening door)
{DIALOGUE}: Did you forget some --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud stands there, filling up the door frame.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: I wondered when you might ring the bell again, Officer White.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: It's Bud.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud looks at Lynn a moment, then down at his own feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Embarrassed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She smiles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: You should see yourself.
{DIALOGUE}: You look like you're ten years old.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud looks back up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn's smile fades as she studies his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's not going to ask questions.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn looks at him a moment more, then runs a hand through the blonde hair covering one eye.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: If you'd called first, I wouldn't look this ridiculous.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LYNN BRACKEN'S (1736 NOTTINGHAM) - BEDROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn comes to Bud naked, her hair brushed back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud goes slow, gently, takes time with his kisses: like she was a lonely woman he wanted to love to death.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn plays off his timing: her kisses back, her touches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally, Bud forces himself to stop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls back so he can see her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: You're wondering if Patchett told me to be receptive.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud doesn't answer, but yes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: It doesn't matter.
{DIALOGUE}: I like you, Bud.
{DIALOGUE}: I really do.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She kisses him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Softly, drawing it out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Not a job.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She wants to make love to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And as Bud stops thinking...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. 5261 CHERAMOYA AVENUE (HOLLYWOOD) - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack sits in his car waiting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He checks his watch... 1:30.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Well past midnight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Come on, Sid.
{DIALOGUE}: Where are you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack decides.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVE WITH him as he gets out and crosses the street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The apartment is dark, the front door a few inches ajar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suspicious, Jack listens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dead quiet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He enters...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. 5261 CHERAMOYA AVENUE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No one here it seems.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Till Jack nearly trips over a body.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Matt Reynolds.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Soaked in blood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Throat slit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack looks down in horror as Reynolds seems to stare back up at him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack stumbles out the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear his CAR DOOR SLAM shut, the SCREECH of RUBBER down the street.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. 2345 HALBORO (HUDGEONS' HOUSE) - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack pounds on Sid's door till lights switch on.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: It's Vincennes!
{DIALOGUE}: Open up!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hudgeons opens the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's in his pajamas.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HUDGEONS
{DIALOGUE}: Jackie!
{DIALOGUE}: You got some good scoop for the Sidster?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Sid, cut the crap.
{DIALOGUE}: I --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HUDGEONS
{DIALOGUE}: Give me some Narco skinny.
{DIALOGUE}: I want to put out an all hop-head issue.
{DIALOGUE}: Shvartze jazz musicians and movie stars.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe tie it into the Rosenbergs.
{DIALOGUE}: You like?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack grabs him, jerks him into the door frame.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Shut up!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HUDGEONS
{META_DATA}: (confused)
{DIALOGUE}: What's wrong, Trash?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HUDGEONS
{DIALOGUE}: What happened with the kid and Loew?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HUDGEONS
{DIALOGUE}: You didn't get my message?
{DIALOGUE}: It got called off.
{DIALOGUE}: The kid chickened out at the last minute.
