{CHARACTER_NAME}: HUDGEONS
{DIALOGUE}: Jackie!
{DIALOGUE}: Big V!
{DIALOGUE}: Let me get my camera!
{DIALOGUE}: Where are you going?!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. AFTER HOURS CLUB - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The BARTENDER walks down the bar to where Jack arrives.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARTENDER
{DIALOGUE}: What'll it be, Jack?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{META_DATA}: (pulls out wallet)
{DIALOGUE}: A bottle of Scotch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the Bartender turns for one, the only bill Jack finds is the President Grant fifty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The things he's done for fifty bucks... As he looks up with despair at his reflection in the bar mirror, the Bartneder sets down a bottle and shot glass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He plucks the fifty from Jack's hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack grabs the bottle and starts out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARTENDER
{DIALOGUE}: Hey!
{DIALOGUE}: Your change!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. 1736 NOTTINGHAM (LYNN BRACKEN'S) - BEDROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spent, Bud and Lynn lie in bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SHe traces a finger over his bicep as he muses on the ceiling.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Who was that guy who was here earlier?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn's tracing finger stops on Bud's shoulder -- a small white scar.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: It doesn't matter.
{DIALOGUE}: All they get is Veronica Lake.
{DIALOGUE}: You got the real Lynn Margaret Bracken...
{META_DATA}: (re: scar)
{DIALOGUE}: Where'd this come from?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: When I was ten, my old man threw a bottle at my mother.
{DIALOGUE}: I guess I got in the way.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: So you saved her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah.
{DIALOGUE}: But not for long.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud looks away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn sees he doesn't want to talk about it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Do you like being a cop, Bud?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: I used to.
{DIALOGUE}: What I do now is strong-arm.
{DIALOGUE}: Sitting duck stuff... No, I don't like it.
{DIALOGUE}: If I could work Homicide like a real detective...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn listens sympathetically.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud's opening up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: There's something wrong with the Nite Owl.
{DIALOGUE}: That prick Exley shot the wrong guys.
{DIALOGUE}: But they made him a hero and whoever killed my partner is still out there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frustrated, Bud pokes at his own chest.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: In here I know it.
{DIALOGUE}: But I can't prove it.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not a detective.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not smart enough.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm just the guy they bring in to scare the other guy shitless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud looks away, embarrassed to have shown so much of himself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn reaches over, turns his face back to her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: You found Patchett.
{DIALOGUE}: You found me.
{DIALOGUE}: You're smart enough.
{DIALOGUE}: Be a detective if that's what you want.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: That simple, huh?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn nods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: That simple.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOLLYWOOD STATION - EXLEY'S OFFICE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley looks up as a CLERK enters holding two files.
