{DIALOGUE}: What do you want to know?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Anything off.
{DIALOGUE}: Anything that didn't make sense.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PINKER
{DIALOGUE}: You mean beside the fact that thirty-five out of forty-five rounds were gratuitous?
{DIALOGUE}: I can't think of anything.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pinker is ticked as Bud steps over to where a group of Nite Owl crime scene photos are posted on the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud pauses at a photo which shows the floor around the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see a high heel shoe, blood smears across the floor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Whose shoe?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PINKER
{DIALOGUE}: Susan Lefferts.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{META_DATA}: (pointing)
{DIALOGUE}: If she was sitting here, then it's facing the wrong way.
{DIALOGUE}: What are these smears in the blood?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PINKER
{DIALOGUE}: It looks like she was flailing, trying to get away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: But she's moving away from the door.
{META_DATA}: (thinks; points)
{DIALOGUE}: Who was sitting at this table?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PINKER
{DIALOGUE}: Dick Stensland.
{META_DATA}: (a beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Had to be dumb panic.
{DIALOGUE}: If she knew him she would've been sitting with him... Right?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud wonders, maybe a puzzle piece just fell into place.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pinker remembers something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PINKER
{DIALOGUE}: You know, there is one thing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pinker rummages a shelf for a glass jar which he hands Bud.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Inside are two wax-saturated cotton balls.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PINKER
{DIALOGUE}: Cotton balls.
{DIALOGUE}: I found them just inside the meat locker door.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Ear plugs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PINKER
{DIALOGUE}: Exactly.
{DIALOGUE}: At least one of those animals had the brains to protect his ears.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: It doesn't exactly play like dumb panic.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PINKER
{DIALOGUE}: What do you mean?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: It's like they knew they were going to kill everyone before they went in...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PINKER
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, so...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud just stares at the picture of Susan Lefferts.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. LEFFERTS' HOUSE (SAN BERNARDINO) - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A shingle shack dump.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud walks the front steps, RINGS the BELL.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hilda Lefferts answers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She doesn't look so good.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Mrs. Lefferts, I'm Officer White with the L.A.P.D. I'd like to ask a couple of questions.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MRS. LEFFERTS
{DIALOGUE}: Let my daughter rest in peace.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Five minutes.
{DIALOGUE}: That's all.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LEFFERTS' HOUSE - LIVING ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pictures of Susan smile down from four walls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vamp poses on a nightclub floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mrs. Lefferts is all twitchy and nervous, her eyes darting to a closed door.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me about the boyfriend she had.
{DIALOGUE}: The one you mentioned at the morgue.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MRS. LEFFERTS
