{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Ma'am, I'm sure she was.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mrs. Lefferts talks directly to a photo of her daughter.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MRS. LEFFERTS
{DIALOGUE}: Susie, I told you I didn't approve of that boyfriend.
{DIALOGUE}: He was too old for you.
{DIALOGUE}: You let him come into this house and be fresh to me.
{DIALOGUE}: I went out one day and old Mrs. Jensen next door saw Susan's boyfriend and another man and thought she heard a ruckus.
