{DIALOGUE}: They were acting nervous.
{DIALOGUE}: And that Stens kept going under the house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Mrs. Lefferts goes shrill, Bud beelines out the door.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. LEFFERTS' HOUSE (SAN BERNARDINO) - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Holding a flashlight, Bud crawls under the house, into...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CRAWLSPACE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud elbow-crawls over the dirt, between wooden pilings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's a long burlap sack ahead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It smells bad.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud rips burlap.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A rat's nest explodes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud sweeps a forearm at them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As they clear, he sees a gristle-caked human skull staring back, a .38 hole in the forehead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Undaunted, Bud tears the burlap back further.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pats the corpse's pockets, comes up with a wallet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud checks the ID.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Turner Meeks."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bus knows him by that name and another.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Buzz Meeks... Holy shit.
