{DIALOGUE}: You talk only to me on this one.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. JACK'S DESK - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sitting in disgust, Jack spots something amidst all the clutter -- the Great Jerk-Off Books of 1962.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He flips one over, looks at the Fleur-de-Lis stamp.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack remembers something Matt Reynolds told him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He dials the phone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah.
{DIALOGUE}: Sergeant Jack Vincennes requesting.
{DIALOGUE}: I need the home address on a Pierce Patchett.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: OPERATOR (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Please hold, Sergeant...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Jack waits, Exley appears in front of him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: I need to speak to you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Give me a minute, will ya?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley clicks off the phone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Damnit... What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: I want you to follow Bud White.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Even I'm not that crazy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: It's not a request.
{DIALOGUE}: I need to know what White knows.
{DIALOGUE}: Follow him or I'll have you pulled off 'Badge of Honor.'
{DIALOGUE}: Permanently.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Yesterday that might've meant something.
{DIALOGUE}: Pull me off.
{DIALOGUE}: You'd be doing me a big favor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Yesterday yes, today no.
{DIALOGUE}: What happened last night?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Transfer me, suspend me.
{DIALOGUE}: Just leave me alone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: You make a mistake?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah.
{DIALOGUE}: My whole life.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack stands, heads out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley follows; he needs help.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Listen, I think I made a mistake, too.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: I ain't a priest, Lieutenant.
{DIALOGUE}: I can't hear your confession.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Do you make the three Negroes for the Nite Owl killings?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: It's a simple question.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: You should be the last person who wants to dig any deeper into the Nite Owl, Lieutenant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley watches as Jack continues down a hall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Rollo Tomasi.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack stops, looks back at him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Is there more to that, or do I have to guess?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Rollo was a purse snatcher.
{DIALOGUE}: My father ran into him off duty.
{DIALOGUE}: He shot my father six times and got away clean.
{DIALOGUE}: No one even knew who he was.
{DIALOGUE}: I made the name up to give him some personality.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: So what's the point?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Rollo's the reason I became a cop.
{DIALOGUE}: I wanted to catch the guys who thought they could get away with it.
{DIALOGUE}: It was supposed to be about truth and justice and Rollo.
{DIALOGUE}: But somewhere along the way I forgot all that... How about you, Jack?
{DIALOGUE}: Why'd you become a cop?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack looks like he might cry, but smiles instead.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: I don't remember...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Both men are quiet a moment.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: I'm trying to figure what angle you're playing this time, but I sure as hell can't see one.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: I've given up angles for awhile.
{DIALOGUE}: I just want to solve this thing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: The Nite Owl was solved, Lieutenant.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: I want to do it right.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: So does Jack.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, college boy, I'll help you.
{DIALOGUE}: But I want half the collar.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: A third.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't think we can make a case without Bud White.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BROWN DERBY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A Packard pulls up out front.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud gets out, heads inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another car pulls up across the street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON JACK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Watching Bud.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack gets out, starts across the street.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BROWN DERBY - BAR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At the bar, Johnny Stompanato looks over as Bud joins him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stompanato isn't happy about it, but he smiles anyway.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOMPANATO
{DIALOGUE}: Wendell White, how's tricks, paesano?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: I ain't your paesano, you wop cocksucker.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nervous, Johnny taps his pinkie ring on a bottle of beer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOMPANATO
{DIALOGUE}: What do you want, officer?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: You remember an ex-cop named Buzz Meeks?
{DIALOGUE}: He works for a guy named Patchett.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Johnny taps his ring harder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bottle almost tips.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOMPANATO
{DIALOGUE}: Should I?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: His file listed you as a known associate.
{DIALOGUE}: Now spill.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOMPANATO
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, yeah.
{DIALOGUE}: That was a long time ago.
{DIALOGUE}: Before your day.
{DIALOGUE}: The last few years he's been muscle for hire.
{DIALOGUE}: But I heard he's disappeared.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: More.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOMPANATO
{DIALOGUE}: More's gonna cost you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud's hand flashes out, grabs Stompanato by the crotch.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: How 'bout I give you your balls back?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOMPANATO
{META_DATA}: (in considerable pain)
{DIALOGUE}: Before Meeks disappeared he was popping off about trying to move eighteen pounds of heroin.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Bullshit.
{DIALOGUE}: Where would a two-bit ex-cop get 18 pounds of heroin?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOMPANATO
{DIALOGUE}: Deuce Perkins.
{DIALOGUE}: Mickey C's narcotics lieutenant.
{DIALOGUE}: The night he got clipped, eighteen pounds of Mickey's heroin went missing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud loosens his grip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stompanato gasps for air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DOOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack peels in, catches a glimpse of Bud and Stompanato.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Too far away too hear anything, Jack quickly ducks out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BAR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stompanato's recovering.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOMPANATO
{DIALOGUE}: Meeks is probably in Rio or someplace like that by now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: He's under a tract house in San Berdoo.
{DIALOGUE}: And he don't smell too good.
{DIALOGUE}: What happened to the heroin, Johnny?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOMPANATO
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know.
{DIALOGUE}: I swear it!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud starts to raise a hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stompanato cringes, but Bud just slaps a twenty down on the bar and goes.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BROWN DERBY - PHONE BOOTH - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack's on the phone to Exley.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: He's in the Brown Derby with Johnny Stompanato.
{META_DATA}: (sees Bud exit)
{DIALOGUE}: Check that.
{DIALOGUE}: I gotta go.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. 1736 NOTTINGHAM (LYNN BRACKEN'S) - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack pulls up, sees Bud knock on the front door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It opens and Bud steps in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack doesn't see who opens it.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BUSHES - 1736 NOTTINGHAM (LYNN BRACKEN'S) - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LEAVES RUSTLE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's movement in the underbrush.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack appears, followed by Exley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack pulls a gun as they near a window.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: What's that for?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Bud White.
{DIALOGUE}: He sees us and we're dead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They press up to the glass for a partial view.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud White sits on a footstool massaging a pair of women's feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack and Exley exchange a long, curious look.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This isn't the Bud White they're used to.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A pair of woman's hands take Bud, the arms covered in glitter and satin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The woman, Lynn Bracken, leans forward to kiss her policeman.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It may have been a long day, but she's every inch Veronica Lake.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Only the hair's not over her eye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They stand, kiss again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn's gown spills down around her ankles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud scoops Lynn into his arms and the two of them disappear into a bedroom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A long beat before...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
