{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Have you discussed this with anyone else, John?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Not even with Exley?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack shakes his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley raises a REVOLVER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He FIRES it at point-blank range, right into Jack's heart.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack hits the floor, his cheek pressed flat on the linoleum.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack opens his mouth to speak.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His lips form the words, but no sound comes out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley crouches down beside him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Have you a valediction, lad?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley leans low, gives Jack an ear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he dies...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Rollo Tomasi...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley frowns in ignorance at the name.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LAPD HEADQUARTERS - BRIEFING ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing mobilizes the police like losing one of their own.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley is at the podium along with Exley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dozens of detectives take notes, including Bud White.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Sergeant Vincennes' body was found in Echo Park at ten o'clock this morning.
{DIALOGUE}: Killed by a single .38 round to the heart.
{DIALOGUE}: One of our own, gentlemen.
{DIALOGUE}: We cannot tolerate it.
{DIALOGUE}: Justice must be swift and merciless.
{DIALOGUE}: That's all.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the men move odd, Dudley approaches Exley.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Edmund, a word with you.
{DIALOGUE}: We received a tip this morning.
{DIALOGUE}: Did Vincennes ever mention the name Rollo Tomasi?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley tries to look like he's thinking as Jack calls from the grave.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Screaming the name Dudley!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: No... Where'd the tip come from?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Anonymous.
{DIALOGUE}: Probably nothing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Dudley moves off, Exley watches him go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Scared.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LAPD HEADQUARTERS - BUD WHITE'S DESK - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud looks over as Dudley sits down across from him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: You're perplexing to me these days, Wendell.
{DIALOGUE}: You're not your old, cruel self anymore.
{DIALOGUE}: I need proof that the extracurricular work I had planned for you remains within your grasp.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: What work?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: I've long been involved in containing hard crime in such a way that myself and a few colleagues might someday enjoy a profit dispensation.
{DIALOGUE}: That day will soon be here and you'll share handsomely.
{DIALOGUE}: Grand means will be in our hands, Wendell.
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Imagine crime limited to the criminal element who perpetrate it.
{DIALOGUE}: Imagine the means to keep the nigger filth sedated.
{DIALOGUE}: But don't stop there.
{DIALOGUE}: Extrapolate.
{DIALOGUE}: Imagine the police in control.
{DIALOGUE}: It's big, lad.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: You lost me, Dudley.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know what you're talking about.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: You have your extracurricular secrets, I have mine.
{DIALOGUE}: We'll hold a clarification session soon.
{DIALOGUE}: For now, I need your fearsome old habits at the Victory Motel.
{DIALOGUE}: We're going to brace a man who may know who killed Jack Vincennes.
{DIALOGUE}: Can I count on you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Sure, boss.
{DIALOGUE}: Sure you can.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FORENSICS LAB - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pinker looks up as Exley enters.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
