{DIALOGUE}: And so what if some homo actor is dead.
{DIALOGUE}: Boys, girls, ten of them step off the bus to L.A. every day.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The MIRROR SPIDERWEBS as Bud slams Loew's face into it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud swings him around, forces him forward and shoves his head in the toilet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He holds it there, finally lets Loew up for breath.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then backhands: one, two, three.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Dudley Smith.
{DIALOGUE}: Spill.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LOEW
{DIALOGUE}: Call him off, Exley!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know how.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: More backhands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Holding Loew by the scruff of the neck, Bud marches him past Exley and back into the...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INNER OFFICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud heaves up the window, practically throws Loew through it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Loew catches hold of the window framing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud hammers his hands loose with a fist and pushes him through.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OUTSIDE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud holds his leg.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Loew screams as coins, comb and wallet spill from his pockets, plummet toward the street below.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INNER OFFICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud shakes Loew, could drop him at any time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Bud...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: If I let you go, there'll be ten more lawyers to take your place tomorrow.
{DIALOGUE}: They just won't come on the bus, that's all.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OUTSIDE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear Loew's PANT LEG TEARING loose.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LOEW
{DIALOGUE}: Okay!
{DIALOGUE}: You're right!
{DIALOGUE}: Dudley's got photos of me and Reynolds.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: What's Dudley's scheme?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: More TEARING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Loew's life may depend on the answer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LOEW
{DIALOGUE}: Dudley's rotten to the core.
{DIALOGUE}: He's taking over Mickey Cohen's rackets, his own hand-picked cops'll be the new franchise holders.
{DIALOGUE}: Because of those pictures I won't be able to prosecute.
{DIALOGUE}: Oh Jesus pull me up!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INNER OFFICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley helps pull Loew back inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud dumps him on the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bruised and bloodied, Loew looks up at Exley.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LOEW
{DIALOGUE}: Dudley's got everyone under his thumb.
{DIALOGUE}: Not just me, but the Chief of Police, the lieutenant governor, everybody!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley pulls his .38, shoves it into the side of Loew's neck.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Not everybody.
{DIALOGUE}: You tip-off Dudley and Officer White visits you alone next time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Loew looks at Bud, nods, his face a bloody mess.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. CITY OFFICE BUILDING - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley and Bud exit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud's wheels are turning.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: They never made a match on the shotgun serial numbers.
{DIALOGUE}: What if Breuning and Carlisle took them from the evidence room?
{DIALOGUE}: Couple of cold pieces that had been hanging around a year or two.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: We should check the records, and, we should talk to Lynn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud just stares at him a beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: You want to talk to her?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud looks away, shakes his head "no."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: You do it.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll check the files.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT - HOLDING ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn looks up as Exley enters.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: her face is puffy, swollen.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{META_DATA}: (dry)
{DIALOGUE}: If I knew you were coming I'd have baked a cake.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Forget everything else for a second, Lynn.
{DIALOGUE}: Is there anything you can give me on Dudley Smith?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A blank look from her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: A police captain.
{DIALOGUE}: I think he's behind all of this.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{META_DATA}: (shakes her head)
{DIALOGUE}: I work for Patchett.
{DIALOGUE}: I had a feeling that there was someone else, but I never knew who.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Okay.
{DIALOGUE}: Look, if it helps, Bud hates himself for what he did.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{META_DATA}: (a beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I know how he feels.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A beat as Exley wonders how he should interpret this.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know if it's pathetic or romantic, but when this is all over I'd like to see you again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn looks away, can't help an ironic smile even as she starts to cry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Exley gives her his handkerchief...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LAPD - EVIDENCE ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud waits at the cage window as a RECORDER returns with some information.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RECORDER
{DIALOGUE}: I got your guns, Bud.
{DIALOGUE}: Signed in April 3rd, 1950.
{DIALOGUE}: Remember the First Western bank robbery?
{DIALOGUE}: They were used in that.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: I want to see them.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RECORDER
{DIALOGUE}: No can do.
{DIALOGUE}: I can't find them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Bud thinks, a ROOKIE-TYPE approaches.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROOKIE-TYPE
{DIALOGUE}: Uh -- Sergeant White?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROOKIE-TYPE
{DIALOGUE}: Dispatch just got a call for you.
{DIALOGUE}: Lieutenant Exley wants you to meet him at the Victory Motel.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VICTORY MOTEL - SUNSET
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud's Packard crests the rise looking down on the Victory.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley's Plymouth is in the courtyard.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. VICTORY MOTEL - ROOM 6 - SUNSET
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley in the hotseat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sitting there thinking.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At a CAR DOOR CLOSING, he goes to the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANOTHER ANGLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley opens the door as Bud approaches, toting a shotgun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sun is down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sky is just a dull glow.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: You wanted to meet here?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Me?
{DIALOGUE}: You called it.
{DIALOGUE}: I got a message that...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the reality sinks in, Bud and Exley hear TIRES on the GRAVEL; CARS are COMING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Being in a concavity, they don't see them yet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then the CARS STOP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But still Bud and Exley can't see anything.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They hear the CLICKS of CAR DOORS OPENING, but they don't hear them shut.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There are FOOTSTEPS, MURMURED WHISPERS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: More CARS PULL UP.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Shit... Come on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley starts for his car, but Bud holds him back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Too late.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Resigned, Exley nods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They retreat back to Room 6, disappear inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's MOVEMENT in the shadows to the left.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: To the right.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. VICTORY MOTEL - ROOM 6 - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's a big back window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud covers most of it with a ratty old mattress.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pumps the shotgun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls a .45 automatic from his waistband.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: Here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He throws the auto to Exley, pulls out a .38.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud's armed for bear.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: You figured this was a set-up?
{DIALOGUE}: And you showed up anyway?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{DIALOGUE}: A lot of bad stuff happened here.
{DIALOGUE}: It's as good a place as any for it to end.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud switches off the light.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They wait in silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: You know, all I ever wanted was to measure up to my father.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD
{META_DATA}: (softly)
{DIALOGUE}: I spent years trying not to live down to mine.
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUD (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (thinking)
{DIALOGUE}: We should block off the bathroom.
{DIALOGUE}: They could come through --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A CREAK outside the front door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud levels the SHOTGUN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The DOOR is BLOWN OFF ITS HINGES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see the figure of a man sprawl back in the dirt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the darkness beyond, MUZZLE FLASHES from all around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley and Bud RETURN FIRE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear the BACK WINDOW BREAK under a MUFFLED BLOW.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud charges back, yanks down the mattress revealing two men climbing through.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sitting ducks: torn apart by THREE TRIPLE-AUGHT ROUNDS close in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A beat, then...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: We got him!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud smiles, in on the plan as theres an answering WHOOP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A third man looks through the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud nails him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud motions Exley to stay put, then slips out the window.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VICTORY MOTEL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud crouches, looks between the cinder blocks supporting the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two sets of feet shuffling along.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud FIRES the SHOTGUN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shrieks as the men go down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud extends the .38 to fire point blank headshots.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud flattens himself as a wicked CROSSFIRE TEARS UP ROOM 6.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. VICTORY MOTEL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley is forced down as well, lying flat as plaster rains down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door frame splinters as more Dudley men charge in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Four men with rifles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One is Patchett's Burly Bodyguard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They spot Exley lying there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hushed whispers as they approach: "Dead meat."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Be careful."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kicks in the side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The men look at each other, sneer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley jerks a foot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The foot man stumbles as Exley spins around SHOOTING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FIRING the .45 and his own .38.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All four men go down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley stands, digs into his pocket to reload.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud scrambles back through the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley looks over and smiles as Bud reloads the shotgun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's dead quiet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: I'm thinking we might walk away from this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At that instant, Dudley steps through the bathroom door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's got Exley dead to rights.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he squeezes the trigger, Bud leaps forward, pushes Exley hard to the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The SHOT passes through Bud's back by his left shoulder blade.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It spins him around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SECOND SHOT to the stomach slows him to a walk as he charges Dudley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A THIRD ROUND SHATTERS Bud's jaw, but still he comes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Driven by rage, his hands reaching for Dudley's throat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He even gets hold before a FOURTH SLUG tears his chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud falls hard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley swings his aim to Exley who's just managed to shake the cobwebs of being flattened by Bud.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A frozen moment.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: I'm loathe to kill my brother officers, Edmund.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Tell that to Jack Vincennes.
{DIALOGUE}: To Stensland.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Jack was a shame, but Dick Stensland had the audacity to try to sell me my own heroin.
{DIALOGUE}: Through his whore girl friend.
{DIALOGUE}: I sent him to make the buy.
{DIALOGUE}: The rest is history.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Why?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: A vacuum, Edmund.
{DIALOGUE}: That's what we have in Los Angeles.
{DIALOGUE}: Sending Mickey Cohen up created it.
{DIALOGUE}: My containment work maintained it.
{DIALOGUE}: Certain photographs guarantee it.
{DIALOGUE}: Organized crime has been held back, but there's still a demand for the services it provides.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: And now you'll provide them.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Absolutely.
{DIALOGUE}: Prostitution and gambling are victimless crimes.
{DIALOGUE}: The heroin we'll run down to the coloreds.
{DIALOGUE}: Anesthetize them.
{DIALOGUE}: As long as it's not a middle class problem, no one will care.
{DIALOGUE}: It's still a crime free city... for respectable people.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley aims the .38, cocks back the hammer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear DISTANT POLICE SIRENS.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: This isn't politics, Edmund.
{DIALOGUE}: There won't be winners and losers when it's over...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley doesn't see Bud stir, reach into a pocket.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Just the living and the dead.
{DIALOGUE}: It's always been that way in the Bureau.
{DIALOGUE}: You should've realized that before you became a detective.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's over.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley's finger tightens on the trigger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But Dudley screams as Bud buries a switchblade into his left calf.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It took all Bud had left.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he collapses...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley wails; Exley dives for Bud's shotgun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley FIRES, misses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A wild SHOTGUN BLAST takes out half the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley stumbles out the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SIRENS BLARE.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VICTORY MOTEL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley drops his gun as the cruisers stream down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley steps out behind him, but doesn't drop the shotgun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two of them are bleached white by headlights.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley raises his badge over his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: We're policemen!
{META_DATA}: (winks)
{DIALOGUE}: Let me do the talking.
{DIALOGUE}: They'll make you Chief of Detectives.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley steps ahead to block his way.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Why not, lad?
{DIALOGUE}: Absolute justice?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Something like that.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Really?
{DIALOGUE}: Would you be willing to rig crime scene evidence to support a prosecuting attorney's working hypothesis?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley doesn't answer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley smiles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Would you be willing to beat confessions out of suspects you knew to be guilty?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley glares.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Laughing, Dudley brushes by, limps toward the gathering policemen.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DUDLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Are you willing to shoot hardened criminals in the back to offset the chance they'll --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The SHOTGUN BELCHES flame.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dudley goes down, shot in the back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley drops the gun, raises his hands over his head.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: L.A. MONTAGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "RAGS TO RICHES" PLAYS.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ROSE BOWL PARADE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Riding in a convertible, waving to the crowds is the Grand Marshal -- the new Vice President, a young Richard Nixon.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. OBSERVATION ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A midnight assembly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Chief, D.A. Loew and several high ranking brass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their attention riveted THROUGH the one-way glass into...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ROOM #1 - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bloody, exhausted, Exley sits across from two INTERNAL AFFAIRS DETECTIVES.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: INTERNAL AFFAIRS #1
{DIALOGUE}: You have a lot of explaining to do, Lieutenant.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{DIALOGUE}: I do.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Exley begins...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TELEVISION SCREEN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Where we're informed that tonight's episode of "Badge of Honor" is: "Dedicated to the memory of technical advisor Sergeant Jack Vincennes."
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VENTURA FREEWAY - CAHUENGA PASS - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A ribbon is cut.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Eager motorists roll down the blacktop.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. GRAUMAN'S CHINESE THEATER - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ronald Reagan applauds as Jane Wyman plunges her hands into fresh sidewalk cement.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. OBSERVATION ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The brass exchange concerned looks and raied eyebrows as they watch Exley THROUGH the glass, his VOICE heard OVER the SPEAKERS.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. UNION STATION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Flatnose Frisco loan shark and Cauliflowered Cleveland enforcer seen earlier at the Victory Motel return to L.A., ready to fill the vacuum.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NEWSSTAND - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hush-Hush is delivered.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The headline: "Actor Reynolds in his Final Role: Conductor of the Night Train to Slice City."
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ROOM #1 - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley stares across at the Internal Affairs Detectives.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: That's it.
{DIALOGUE}: That's the whole story.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Exley looks to the gray-tinted wall mirror...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OBSERVATION ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Loew leans over, whispers to the Chief.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LOEW
{DIALOGUE}: The press would have a field day with this.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHIEF
{META_DATA}: (a beat)
{DIALOGUE}: When in doubt, feed them a hero.
{DIALOGUE}: In this case, we'll need more than one.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOS ANGELES EXAMINER HEADLINE:
{META_DATA}: R.I.P. DUDLEY SMITH Fabled L.A. Cop Dies Defending City from Organized Crime!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LAPD HEADQUARTERS - BRIEFING ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley in his dress blue uniform.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Chief smiles, pins gold stars to his shoulders.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHIEF
{DIALOGUE}: Captain Edmund Exley.
{DIALOGUE}: Chief of Detectives.
{DIALOGUE}: Los Angeles Police Department.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Applause.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Flashbulbs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn watches from the back as Exley runs a handshake gauntlet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally, he spots her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's returned to her natural brunette.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looks even better.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley steps over.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{META_DATA}: (ironic smile)
{DIALOGUE}: I tried to throw it all away and they give it back in spades.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. PARKING LOT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley walks Lynn out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Where will you go?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Bisbee, Arizona.
{DIALOGUE}: The air's good for pensioners and I know where everything is.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: When?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Right now, before I back down.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Where is he?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lynn gestures ahead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They walk to her car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She opens the back door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud's in the back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Braces on his legs, head sutured.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jaw wired shut and tubes running in and out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But his hands still look strong.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud forces a smile through the wires, tries to say something, but can't.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks for the push.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley takes his hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud squeezes till both men wince.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: You just did what you did.
{DIALOGUE}: No rank, no glory.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley slips his Medal of Valor into Bud's hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: From me to you.
{DIALOGUE}: It'll mean something if it's yours.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud takes it, turns away so Exley won't see the tears.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: We should go now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Exley steps back, Lynn closes the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PARTY noises drift from upstairs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley looks to Lynn.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EXLEY
{DIALOGUE}: Do you think I ever could've been in the running?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LYNN
{DIALOGUE}: Some men get the world.
{DIALOGUE}: Others get ex-hookers and a trip to Arizona.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley wishes he'd gotten the trip to Arizona.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She kisses him on the cheek, gets in the CAR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: STARTS it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley looks back at Bud.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bud presses his hands to the glass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley touches his side, palms half the man's size.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hands against hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The car moves.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A turn into traffic, a good-bye TOOT on the HORN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Exley's all alone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he watches them go...
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK.
{META_DATA}: THE END
